<br>
<br>
Listen...um...Misty. When countries fight wars, the actual land mass of that country doesn't necessarily heave up and throw itself at the other land masses involved. No offense, but your English really isn't good enough to play semantic games. The United States was fighting a war.<br>
<br>
Whether or not a war takes place on your own soil has NOTHING TO DO WITH IT, IDIOT. By that definition, Germany wasn't fighting a war until the Allies crossed into the Rhine.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <br>
